SB NO. 406 ENROLLED
1 C. The governing authority may enter into a contract with any public
2 entity authorized to collect sales or use taxes, under terms and conditions it
3 considers appropriate, including payment of a reasonable collection fee for the
4 collection of the hotel occupancy tax authorized by this Section. The hotel
5 occupancy tax shall be in addition to all taxes levied upon the occupancy of hotel
6 rooms located within the city.
7 D. Except as provided in Subsection C of this Section, the governing
8 authority of the city shall use the proceeds of the tax to fund the construction,
9 operation, and maintenance of recreational facilities in the city or other
10 tourism-related initiatives set forth in the proposition authorizing the levy of
11 such tax.
12 Section 2. This Act shall become effective upon signature by the governor or, if not
13 signed by the governor, upon expiration of the time for bills to become law without signature
14 by the governor, as provided by Article III, Section 18 of the Constitution of Louisiana. If
15 vetoed by the governor and subsequently approved by the legislature, this Act shall become
16 effective on the day following such approval.
